{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tj8PYehvwYsq1hgR2EVsSg","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beet and Orange Salad.generated.18.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08cfdd1d-4a87-41d6-bcd8-0b7631cc671a","uuid":"9a833eea-a810-4604-883a-2ffd363e47ce","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beet and Orange Salad.generated.18.txt","content":"Spring Salads | Light Lunch | Vegetarian\nPRZYGOTOWANIE 15 MIN\n\nBEET AND ORANGE SALAD\n\nServes: 4-6 | Chill time: 30 minutes\n\nINGREDIENTS\n\n4 medium beets, roasted and peeled\n2 large oranges, peeled and segmented\n4 cups fresh mixed greens (arugula, spinach, butter lettuce)\n1/2 red onion, thinly sliced\n1/4 cup crumbled goat cheese\n1/4 cup candied walnuts or pecans\n\nFOR THE VINAIGRETTE\n\n3 tablespoons fresh orange juice\n2 tablespoons red wine vinegar\n1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n1 shallot, minced\n1/4 cup extra virgin olive oil\nSalt and pepper to taste\n1/2 teaspoon honey\n\nASSEMBLY\n\n1. Cut roasted beets into wedges\n2. Arrange mixed greens on individual plates or serving platter\n3. Top with beet wedges and orange segments\n4. Scatter red onion slices over greens\n5. Whisk together orange juice, vinegar, mustard, and shallot\n6. Slowly drizzle in olive oil while whisking\n7. Season with salt, pepper, and honey\n8. Dress salad just before serving\n9. Top with goat cheese and candied nuts\n10. Serve immediately while greens are fresh and crisp\n\nTIPS\n\nFor a meal-prep version, keep components separate and assemble just before eating.\nThe beets and oranges can be prepared up to 2 days in advance.\nSubstitute walnuts with almonds or pumpkin seeds as preferred.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
